        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RAM Identification Guide -->
  <section id="identify-ram" class="identification-guide">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">How to Identify Your RAM</h2>
      
      <div class="guide-content">
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subtitle">Method 1: Check the Label</h3>
          <div class="guide-text">
            <p>Most RAM modules have a label with key specifications:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Memory Type:</strong> Look for "DDR3", "DDR4", or "DDR5"</li>
              <li><strong>Capacity:</strong> Usually shown as "4GB", "8GB", "16GB", etc.</li>
              <li><strong>Speed:</strong> Listed as "PC3-12800", "DDR4-3200", or similar</li>
              <li><strong>Brand:</strong> Manufacturer name (Corsair, Kingston, etc.)</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tip-box">
              <strong>üí° Tip:</strong> The label is usually on a sticker on the side of the RAM module. 
              If it's hard to read, try taking a photo with your phone's camera for better zoom.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subtitle">Method 2: Use System Information</h3>
          <div class="guide-text">
            <p>Check your computer's system information:</p>
            <div class="os-tabs">
              <div class="os-tab">
                <h4>Windows</h4>
                <ol>
                  <li>Press Windows + R, type "msinfo32"</li>
                  <li>Look for "Installed Physical Memory"</li>
                  <li>Or use Task Manager ‚Üí Performance ‚Üí Memory</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
              <div class="os-tab">
                <h4>Mac</h4>
                <ol>
                  <li>Apple Menu ‚Üí About This Mac</li>
                  <li>Click "Memory" tab for details</li>
                  <li>Or use System Information app</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
              <div class="os-tab">
                <h4>Linux</h4>
                <ol>
                  <li>Terminal: <code>sudo dmidecode -t memory</code></li>
                  <li>Or: <code>lshw -short -C memory</code></li>
                  <li>GUI: System Monitor ‚Üí Hardware tab</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subtitle">Method 3: Physical Inspection</h3>
          <div class="guide-text">
            <p>Identify RAM type by physical characteristics:</p>
            <div class="ram-types">
              <div class="ram-type">
                <h4>DDR3</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>240 pins (desktop) or 204 pins (laptop)</li>
                  <li>Notch positioned left of center</li>
                  <li>Common speeds: 1333MHz, 1600MHz</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="ram-type">
                <h4>DDR4</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>288 pins (desktop) or 260 pins (laptop)</li>
                  <li>Notch positioned right of center</li>
                  <li>Common speeds: 2133MHz, 2400MHz, 3200MHz</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="ram-type">
                <h4>DDR5</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>288 pins (desktop) or 262 pins (laptop)</li>
                  <li>Different notch position than DDR4</li>
                  <li>Common speeds: 4800MHz, 5600MHz, 6400MHz</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-grid">
        <div class="faq-category">
          <h3 class="faq-category-title">General Questions</h3>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              How quickly do I get paid after shipping my RAM?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Once we receive and test your RAM modules, payment is processed within 2 business days. 
              We offer PayPal, bank transfer, or check payment options.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What happens if my RAM doesn't match the quote?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>If the actual condition or specifications differ from your submission, we'll contact you 
              with a revised offer. You can accept the new price or have your RAM returned at no cost.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              Do you buy RAM from businesses or just individuals?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>We purchase RAM from both individuals and businesses. For bulk quantities over 50 modules, 
              please contact us directly for special pricing and logistics arrangements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-category">
          <h3 class="faq-category-title">Technical Questions</h3>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              Can I sell RAM that's currently installed in my computer?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes, but make sure you have replacement RAM or don't need the computer operational. 
              We recommend backing up important data before removing memory modules.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What if I don't know the exact speed of my RAM?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>No problem! Use our identification guide above, or select "Unknown" in the form. 
              Our technicians will identify the exact specifications when we receive your modules.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              Do you accept ECC or server memory?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes! We purchase ECC (Error-Correcting Code) memory, registered DIMMs, and other 
              server-grade memory. These often have higher value due to specialized applications.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What's the difference between single and dual-rank memory?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Rank refers to how memory chips are organized on the module. This affects compatibility 
              and performance but doesn't significantly impact resale value for most consumer RAM.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-category">
          <h3 class="faq-category-title">Shipping & Logistics</h3>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              How should I package RAM for shipping?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Use anti-static bags if available, or wrap in aluminum foil. Place in a sturdy box 
              with padding. Avoid bubble wrap directly touching the modules as it can create static.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              Do you provide prepaid shipping labels?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>For orders over $100 estimated value, we provide prepaid shipping labels. 
              For smaller orders, shipping costs are deducted from your final payment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
              What if my package gets lost in shipping?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>We recommend using tracked shipping services. If using our prepaid labels, 
              packages are automatically insured. For self-shipped items, consider purchasing insurance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
